<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>3-1206.04</num>
  <heading>Authorized acts.</heading>
  <text>An advanced practice registered nurse may:</text>
  <para>
    <num>(1)</num>
    <text>Initiate, monitor, and alter drug therapies;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(2)</num>
    <text>Initiate appropriate therapies or treatments;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(3)</num>
    <text>Make referrals for appropriate therapies or treatments;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(4)</num>
    <text>Perform additional functions within his or her specialty determined in accordance with rules and regulations promulgated by the board; and</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 6-99" type="History" path="§604">Mar. 25, 1986, D.C. Law 6-99, § 604, 33 DCR 729</annotation>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 10-247" type="History">Mar. 23, 1995, D.C. Law 10-247, § 2(s), 42 DCR 457</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 2-3306.4.</annotation>
    <annotation app="2018-02-17" doc="D.C. Law 22-60" eff="2018-02-17" path="§2|(a)" type="History"/>
    <annotation app="2018-02-17" doc="D.C. Law 22-60" eff="2018-02-17" path="§2|(b)" type="History"/>
    <annotation app="2018-02-17" doc="D.C. Law 22-60" eff="2018-02-17" path="§2|(c)" type="History"/>
  </annotations>
  <para>
    <num>(5)</num>
    <text>Sign, certify, stamp, or endorse all documents that require a signature by a physician, in place of a physician, provided it is within the scope of their authorized practice.</text>
  </para>
</section>
